The paper presents a model-based testing approach that involves building test models using a full programming language and domain-specific concepts. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category, as it deals with software testing and model-based development. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of a framework with modeling elements, which could indicate a focus on Programming Languages (cs.PL). The use of automated test generation and domain-specific modeling language also suggests a potential overlap with Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-categories. Finally, the paper's emphasis on generating test cases using concepts familiar to domain experts could indicate a connection to Machine Learning (cs.LG), as this sub-category often involves incorporating domain-specific knowledge into models.
